{
    "Body": "Chief Compliance Officer Toronto / Compliance Team / Full Time Apply for this job Coinsquare Capital Markets (\u201cCSCM\u201d) is looking for a Chief Compliance Officer to lead its pending IIROC Investment Dealer and OSC registered Marketplace. The CCO candidate will play a critical role in guiding and shaping both the compliance and regulatory function/structure at CSCM as it relates to the regulation and trading of digital assets in Canada. Reporting directly to the CEO, the CCO will be responsible for establishing and overseeing compliance with all regulatory requirements as it relates to both dealer and marketplace activities and will be a key member of the Executive team. Responsibilities Lead the compliance function for all matters related to CSCM, including, but not limited to, building and developing a Compliance team that will be responsible for day-to-day compliance oversight and testing across the investment dealer and marketplace business units; Provide strategic regulatory guidance and advice to the Executive team and relevant stakeholders and serve as the main point of contact for applicable regulatory authorities; Organize, present and build awareness around regulatory compliance through training and cultural initiatives; Create and build a compelling vision and strategy for the future for CSCM and develop distinctive strategies to achieve desired business outcomes; Promote and encourage innovation at all levels of the business and influence teams to adopt new processes and procedures required to shape and grow the business; Establish, update and provide expert regulatory advice on compliance policies and procedures as required to ensure, to every extent possible, that CSCM is compliant with applicable laws, rules and regulations that are responsive to IIROC / OSC / CSA rules, policies, guidance and requirements; Manage investigations, coordinate fact gathering, and provide responses to periodic regulatory inquiries; Represent CSCM at industry related meetings, events and conferences; Requirements A Bachelor of Law, Chartered Accountant, Chartered Financial Analyst, or Master of Business Administration preferred; Significant experience in leading a successful compliance program at an IIROC registered investment dealer and/or a registered alternative trading system (\u201cATS\u201d); Working knowledge of the relevant issues, laws, regulations and guidelines affecting compliance, risk management and market conduct in the digital asset industry; Experience building and mentoring high performing compliance teams; Successful completion of the Canadian Securities Course (CSC); Successful completion of the Chief Compliance Officers Qualifying Exam; Successful completion of the Partners, Directors and Senior Officers Course (PDO); Experience acting as a liaison with regulatory bodies on interpretation, application and level of adherence to laws and regulations; Proven experience in managing risk and compliance issues within a regulated business and implementing such compliance programs; Nice To Haves Exposure to Fintech or digital asset regulations and requirements Coinsquare is Canada\u2019s leading and most secure digital asset trading platform for trading Bitcoin, Ethereum, Litecoin and other digital currencies. We built the most secure trading platform, and since our founding in 2014 we\u2019ve never lost a coin. We\u2019re FINTRAC regulated as a money services business, meaning we keep all our clients' money in Canada and use bank-level security measures on our platform. Discover what's possible with digital currency by checking out our trading platform: Coinsquare for Android | iOS | Web We\u2019re full of bright and diverse thinkers. Team members have equal opportunities to contribute to our success within a scale-up culture that encourages self-starters, transparency and team connectivity. We know diverse teams make strong teams. We welcome people of diverse backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. If you require accommodation during the application process, simply let us know and we\u2019ll ensure it\u2019s a positive experience for you. In order to promote and enhance the security of Coinsquare and our platform, just so you know, anyone receiving a job offer will be required to complete a background check. Apply for this job Coinsquare Home PageJobs powered by", 
